manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Fall in love with our award winning WubbaNub Pacifier, the original part plush, part pacifier. The patented WubbaNub design is sure to be your baby’s first friend. The unique style of the original WubbaNub Pacifier allows it to remain near baby’s mouth, easy to grasp, nearly impossible to lose and may assist baby to self soothe. WubbaNub is distributed in hospitals, NICU and well-baby units nationwide and is made with a 100% silicone pacifier, a non-latex and BPA, PVC and Phthalate-free. The durable one-piece construction of the pacifier means no germs hiding between cracks. WubbaNub is a safety-first company that mandates all infant/baby products are completely safety tested. NOTE: WubbaNub Pacifiers purchased online are packaged in a clear pouch that further describes features and benefits.

MONSTER SQUAD Tons of love in every Wub! Wubbanub pacifiers are easier to hold on to and harder to lose. Our limited-edition Monster Squad can’t scare us. Literally! They're way too sweet and smiley. Bright in color and silly in appearance, this endearing creature has little legs, making him easy for teeny-tiny hands to hold onto. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to Find Color
reviews.reviewText: Love the bright color. Makes it easy to find when baby needs it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Grandbaby loves these!!
reviews.reviewText: These have become a favorite for grandbabies. Each one is adorable, easy to wipe clean, and if too dirty we toss in the wash and air dry. My favorite is the bear in pajamas. :) They r easy to grasp, don't fall through crib rails, and provide huggable comfort, too.I previously posted a review/comment about not receiving my order, then it arrived the next day. If I find the previous review, hopefully I can remove it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2018
reviews.reviewText: This is the only type of pacifier my 3 month old will hold in her mouth. I bought her this so that she can hold onto it and put it back in herself while in the car or falling asleep (which she's working on :)) The material of the "monster" is very soft. The pacifier is attatched very strongly to the plush. Its cute and I hope she continues to use it. To clean I just wipe the plush with a damp cloth with a tiny bit of dish soap and wash the pacifier with soap and hot water then let air dry. We may purchase more in the future if needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars and this one is just as fantastic and cute as the others
reviews.reviewText: I have had a Wubbanub for all of my children, and this one is just as fantastic and cute as the others. It's nice to have a binky that won't get lost, since it's stuck to a soft purple monster. Not only is it easy for my baby to hold, and stays with her when she's bundled, but friends/neighbors/family members always know if we've misplaced our binky. :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An essential for your baby registry
reviews.reviewText: These pacifiers are so cute. Although I would like to figure out how to attach a clip to it to clip to my baby it would be the perfect baby essential. But I just love them. There so many cute animals to choose from and our son loves them. (They are also easy to find in the middle of the night when searching for the soothing tool to make the baby go back to sleep)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Both daughter’s have loved these pacifiers!
reviews.reviewText: Both of my daughter’s have used these and we absolutely love them. We would swaddle them with these tucked in right by their mouths so they were right there when they spit them out and we no longer had to get up in the middle of the night to put it back in their mouth when they were tiny. My youngest was able to put it back in her mouth by the time she was 2 months old. They are so much easier to find when dropped and so easy to clean. I just throw them in the washing machine with a load of clothes and then hand wash the pacifier. They dry super fast and are dry enough straight from the washer that when they were older I would just hand them back. Between the two of them we’ve probably bought at least 20. I love them as much as they do. Ha ha! I always give as gifts and my friends have all liked them as much as we do.
